==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Dorsiferous
<hw>Dor*sif"er*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>,. <ety>[<ets>Dorsum</ets> +
<ets>-ferous</ets>; cf. F. <ets>dorsif⟦egrave⟧re</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>Bearing, or producing, on the back; -- applied
to ferns which produce seeds on the back of the leaf, and to certain
Batrachia, the ova of which become attached to the skin of the back of
the parent, where they develop; dorsiparous.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dorsimeson</ent>⟦br⟧
